review_blob: Pours bright ruby with little to no head that has somewhat of a lacing. Aroma is soft with sweet berry fruits and a floral note. The taste is dense and fruity, just like a carbonated liquorish raspberry syrup with a light malty finish and soft aftertaste! This is just perfect for the warm season!

Beautiful bourbon aroma with notes of caramel and sour cherries. Pours hazy deep brown with a very short head that laces slightly. Tastes wonderfully, sweet damn! Starts with a bourbon kick thats wrapped in caramel and oak, then finishes with a profound chocolate finish. Weak medium body with decent carbonation and a brandy finish to it. One of the best brews Ive had!

Pours deep brown with a light beige head that produces some lacing. Has a roast aroma, which is not very strong. The definite ash toast and smokey malty aroma is in match with a very citrus flavor, but dont expect a traditional orange flavor. Either way I appreciate that it gives it an interesting complexity. It has a medium body with a creamy texture, medium carbonation and a stingy citrus finish.
beer_name: James Brown Brews Chocolate Orange Stout

review_blob: Pours a clear pale gold with medium carbonation and a very small head that dissipates quickly; low carbonation. The aroma is grainy, sweet, with a slight floral, soft hoppy finish. An interesting take on the classical Kristallweizen, but doesnt offer much in return.
Pours hazy with a golden-brass color and a soft head that laces and dissipates quickly. Hop aroma is citrus with slight sweet malt notes. Has a dry bitter finish, and the alcohol is fairly masked.

Pours deep brown with opaque clarity. The delicate head is 2 fingers but dissipates quickly. First note in the aroma is a alcoholic, which is a bit unmasked by the coffee and cereal 2nd notes. Has a dry finish.

Served from a bottle. Black color; head dissipates quickly; A slight woody hop aroma that blends in with the chocolate and coffee from the malt. It has a balanced towards delicate mouthfeel with a slightly sour finish.
